        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 5:02PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 502 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Winona Lake, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Warsaw, Winona Lake, Pierceton, Silver Lake, Claypool, Larwill,
Burket, Sidney, Big Barbee Lake, Little Chapman Lake, Ridinger Lake,
Monoquet, Irish Lake, Palestine, Big Chapman Lake, Sechrist Lake,
Packerton, and Wooster.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
